Reasoning: The paper discusses a Selective Dissemination of Information service for Institutional Repositories and Digital Libraries, which involves identifying user context and offering them new documents and resources. This involves the use of an Ontology-based Context Aware system, which suggests a focus on Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL). The system also involves an inference engine, which suggests the use of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the system aims to improve user experience and offer personalized recommendations, which suggests a focus on Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
